stylometry: A genetic algorithm is a method of searching an optimization model's feasible region for an optimal solution. A genetic algorithm can be set as a percent, such as 5%, and this means that Solver is within 5% of the optimal solution. A genetic algorithm helps solve problems in Evolutionary Solver. Evolutionary Solver is important when solving non-linear model problems because it uses the genetic algorithm to find the global maxima within several local maxima. Evolutionary Solver is important because it allows us to solve non-linear models and set a start value, as well as change certain option information (such as speed and length of time the solver is run).
